echoflow (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add live and segmented Qwen transcription so recognition can progress
    during recording and long dictation returns stable text sooner.
  * Add microphone source selection with friendly device names and a fallback
    source query so users can choose the intended PipeWire input reliably.
  * Add a stream mode switch and live text preview in the voice capsule while
    keeping final committed text based on completed recognition.
  * Apply settings changes by restarting the service and hide unavailable
    microphones to prevent silent recordings from disconnected inputs.
  * Improve speech detection for quiet or DC-offset microphone audio and make
    live recording shutdown bounded when workers or PipeWire cleanup stall.
  * Add an EchoFlow tray logo and remove unused recognition settings from the
    settings dialog.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:29:29 +0800

echoflow (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of EchoFlow, an offline voice input method for
    deepin/Fcitx5 powered by the Qwen ASR runtime.
  * Download and manage 0.6B/1.7B Qwen ASR models directly from the
    settings UI, replacing the legacy setup script.
  * Toggle recording with right-Ctrl and get visual feedback through an
    animated capsule tooltip near the cursor.
  * DTK-integrated settings dialog that follows system theme colors.
  * Native C++17 service with tuned ASR startup and OpenBLAS latency.
  * CMake-backed Debian packaging with a GitHub Actions release workflow.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 09:30:00 +0800
